### Description

I have created three Angular projects. The first one is in Angular 17, which serves as my sidebar. The second and third projects are both in Angular 18; the second project contains several modules with routing, and the third project includes some lists and tables. These Angular applications have been converted into Angular elements.

I want to use all of these elements in a single Angular 18 application. However, I am encountering an issue with routing from the parent application. I have added scripts to handle route changes from the Angular 17 elements to the Angular 18 elements, but when I use the browser's back button to change routes, I encounter an error when multiple version of angular elements are loaded.



